abstract: North Korea wins its first gold medal at world aquatics championships as Kim Kuk-hyang wins women's 10-meter diving event.
lead_paragraph: North Korea took its first gold medal at the world aquatics championships in Kazan, Russia, as Kim Kuk-hyang, 16, won the women’s 10-meter diving.

headline.main: North Korea Wins First Aquatics Gold
headline.print_headline: Sports Briefing | Diving; North Korea Wins First Aquatics Gold
